y synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Flamville was born in 1060. He had at least 1 son. He died before 1130."},"et":{"Cir 1060–Bef 1130":"1060–enne 1130","1094–1130":"1094–1130","1060–1130":"1060–1130","Bef 1130":"enne 1130","Cir 1060":"1060","1130":"1130","1094":"1094","1060":"1060"},"fi":{"Cir 1060–Bef 1130":"1060–ennen vuotta 1130","1094–1130":"1094–1130","1060–1130":"1060–1130","Bef 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","Cir 1060":"1060","1130":"1130","1094":"1094","1060":"1060"},"fr":{"Cir 1060–Bef 1130":"1060–avant 1130","1094–1130":"1094–1130","1060–1130":"1060–1130","Bef 1130":"avant 1130","Cir 1060":"1060","1130":"1130","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","lifeSummary":"Robert de Flamville est né en 1060. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé avant 1130."},"de":{"Cir 1060–Bef 1130":"1060–vor 1130","1094–1130":"1094–1130","1060–1130":"1060–1130","Bef 1130":"vor 1130","Cir 1060":"1060","1130":"1130","1094":"1094","1060":"1060","lifeSummary":"Robert de Flamville wurde 1060 geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb vor 1130."},"ht":{"Cir 1060–Bef 1130":"1060–before 1130","1094–1130":"1094–1130","1060–1130":"1060–1130","Bef 1130":"before 113